<keyStep id="F1292E48B835FFC5FF1DE9E8B1AFFE63" box="[136,1451,443,465]" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">1. Annulus present ..................................................................................................................................................................................2</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6236EDB835FFC5FF1DE98BB1AFFE5E" blockId="7.[136,1451,443,1069]" box="[136,1451,471,493]" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">
<keyLead id="F12C95D8B835FFC5FF1DE98BB1AFFE5E" box="[136,1451,471,493]" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">
<keyStep id="F1292E48B835FFC5FF1DE98BB1AFFE5E" box="[136,1451,471,493]" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">2. Annulus typically membranous and persistent...................................................................................................................................3</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<keyStep id="F1292E48B835FFC5FF1DE9A7B1AEFD94" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">
<paragraph id="4A6236EDB835FFC5FF1DE9A7B1AEFDB9" blockId="7.[136,1451,443,1069]" box="[136,1450,500,522]" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">
<keyLead id="F12C95D8B835FFC5FF1DE9A7B1AEFDB9" box="[136,1450,500,522]" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">
3. Cap nearly white, central yellowish brown; spores 12–16 × 8–10 μm, wide ellipse to nearly hexagonal......................... 
<taxonomicName id="8DDD4D6EB835FFC5FAABE9A6B1AEFDB9" box="[1342,1450,500,522]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenogastraceae" genus="Psilocybe" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="cubensis">
<emphasis id="78A9EAFFB835FFC5FAABE9A6B1AEFDB9" bold="true" box="[1342,1450,500,522]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">P. cubensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6236EDB835FFC5FF1DEA42B1AEFD94" blockId="7.[136,1451,443,1069]" box="[136,1450,529,551]" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">
<keyLead id="F12C95D8B835FFC5FF1DEA42B1AEFD94" box="[136,1450,529,551]" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">
3. Spores 8–10 × 5–6 μm, subovoid to subrhomboid.................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="8DDD4D6EB835FFC5FA9FEA42B1AEFD94" box="[1290,1450,529,551]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenogastraceae" genus="Psilocybe" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="wayanadensis">
<emphasis id="78A9EAFFB835FFC5FA9FEA42B1AEFD94" bold="true" box="[1290,1450,529,551]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">P. wayanadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="F1292E48B835FFC5FF1DEA7DB1AFFDD3" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">
