<keyLead id="F12C95D8B835FFC5FF1DEA7DB1AEFDF0" box="[136,1450,558,580]" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">
2. Annulus fall off easily; without caulocystidia or pleurocystidia; spores 11.5–13.5 × 7–8 µm, oval in face .................... 
<taxonomicName id="8DDD4D6EB835FFC5FAAFEA7DB1AEFDF0" box="[1338,1450,558,579]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenogastraceae" genus="Psilocybe" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="venenata">
<emphasis id="78A9EAFFB835FFC5FAAFEA7DB1AEFDF0" bold="true" box="[1338,1450,558,579]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">P. venenata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6236EDB835FFC5FF1DEA18B1AFFDD3" blockId="7.[136,1451,443,1069]" box="[136,1451,586,609]" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">
<keyLead id="F12C95D8B835FFC5FF1DEA18B1AFFDD3" box="[136,1451,586,609]" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">
